quran[19]{c,v,t}:
  73,1,You who are enwrapped in your clothing
  73,2,"stay up at night, except a little"
  73,3,"half of it, or a little less"
  73,4,"or a little more, and recite the Qur´an distinctly"
  73,5,We will impose a weighty Word upon you
  73,6,Certainly rising at night has a stronger effect and is more conducive to concentration
  73,7,In the daytime much of your time is taken up by business matters
  73,8,"Remember the Name of your Lord, and devote yourself to Him completely"
  73,9,Lord of the East and West — there is no god but Him — so take Him as your Guardian
  73,10,Be steadfast in the face of what they say and cut yourself off from them — but courteously
  73,11,"Leave the deniers, who live a life of ease, to Me, alone, and tolerate them a little longer"
  73,12,With Us there are shackles and a Blazing Fire
  73,13,and food that chokes and a painful punishment
  73,14,on the Day the earth and mountains shake and the mountains become like shifting dunes
  73,15,We have sent you a Messenger to bear witness against you just as We sent Pharaoh a Messenger
  73,16,"But Pharaoh disobeyed the Messenger, so We seized him with terrible severity"
  73,17,"How will you safeguard yourselves, if you are kafir, against a Day which will turn children grey"
  73,18,by which heaven will be split apart? His promise will be fulfilled
  73,19,"This truly is a reminder, so let anyone who wills take the Way towards his Lord"